.TH sqsh-mk 1 "May 27, 2024" "Version @VERSION@" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
sqsh-mk \- create a squashfs archive

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sqsh-mk
[\fB-v\fR]
\fIFILE...\fR \fIARCHIVE\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sqsh-mk
creates a squashfs archive from one or more files. The last argument
specifies the output archive. Each preceding file is stored in the root of the
archive using its basename.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -v ", " --version
Print the version of \fBsqsh-mk\fR and exit.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The \fBsqsh-mk\fR command exits with 0 on success and non-zero on failure.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sqsh-cat (1),
.BR sqsh-ls (1)

